<p class="Sitemapheader">Launch of DESD website</p>
<h2>&nbsp;</h2>
<div id="maincontenttext"><P></P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>As you are aware, the Decade 2005 -  2014 has been declared as the &quot;UN Decade of Education for Sustainable  Development&quot; (UNDESD). The goal of the UNDESD is to integrate the  principles, values and practices of Sustainable Development into all aspects of  education and learning.</P>
<p>CEE has recently developed a website  in order to promote public awareness and engage a large number of stakeholders  to participate actively and contribute to the Decade. This website <a href="http://www.desd.org/">www.desd.org</a> aims at establishing a strong online community for networking and sharing of  knowledge on Sustainable Development by linking learners, practitioners, researchers,  policy-makers and activists. Apart from providing information and resources on  the Decade, this website would be a knowledge platform to discuss ESD issues  and seek expert advice in the case of problem areas. These discussions would  then be channeled into actionable objectives to lay a road-map for the Decade.</p>
<p>Your inputs in the form of  discussion and debates in the website would contribute greatly towards the  development of the knowledge platform that we hope the website will create. We  invite you to participate in the debates and discussions in order to strengthen  Education for Sustainable Development. Contact <a href="mailto:esf@ceeindia.org">desd@ceeindia.org</a> for any clarifications.<br />
  &nbsp;  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />
  Regards,</p>
<p>Kartikeya V. Sarabhai<br />
  Director</p>
<p>Centre for  Environment Education Nehru Foundation for Development Thaltej Tekra Ahmedabad  - 380 054 Ph: +91-79 - 2685 8002 to 09 Fax: +91 - 79 - 2685 8010 <a href="http://www.ceeindia.org/">www.ceeindia.org</a><br />
  CEE is a national institution supported by the  Ministry of Environment and Forests (MoEF), Government of India. CEE's primary  mandate is to improve public awareness and understanding of the environment  with a view to promoting the conservation and sustainable use of nature and  natural resources. Towards this, CEE develops innovative programmes,  educational material, undertakes demonstration projects and builds capacities  in the field of environmental education. CEE is the nodal agency for  implementation of DESD in India.</p>
<p>ESD-website: <a href="http://www.desd.org/">www.desd.org</a></p>
